id: pm-mi2x
title: "Scale benchmark harness: synthetic 10k/100k/1M-item workspace generator + latency/memory/token baseline for the read and claim hot paths"
description: "Do-first measurement child of pm-9rxu (mirrors the pm-a22j token-baseline pattern from pm-n7rr): no optimization lands without before/after numbers from this harness. Duplicate check: no existing benchmark/perf-harness item covers workspace-size scaling (pm-4oww measured extension latency only)."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:storage",benchmark,performance,scale
created_at: "2026-07-06T21:24:53.754Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-11T10:38:41.683Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 600
acceptance_criteria: "Repeatable script/harness generates synthetic workspaces at 10k/100k/1M items (realistic type/status/tag/parent distribution, history streams included); measures p50/p95 wall time, peak RSS, and output token count for context/next/list/search/get/create/claim; baseline numbers recorded on the epic (pm notes) and in a committed report; harness runs from a clean checkout without touching the real workspace"
parent: pm-9rxu
risk: low
confidence: high
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T10:27:04.254Z",maintainer-agent,"Slicing (S1-S4), performance-program entry point per pm-9rxu delivery order step 1.\n\nS1 generator (~150m): deterministic seeded synthetic-workspace generator at 10k/100k/1M items. Shape distributions derived from THIS workspace (~1.7k items) scaled up: type mix, status partition (~85% closed at maturity), dep-graph fan-in/out, tag cardinality, history-stream lengths, body sizes. Two write modes: SDK-path (exercises real mutation code, honest but slow - fine to 10k) and direct-layout fast mode for 100k/1M (must produce byte-identical layout; verify with pm validate). Lives in scripts/bench/, runs from clean checkout, never touches the real workspace (withTempPmPath pattern - realpath the root, see pm-dprb).\n\nS2 measurement runner (~120m): per-tier runs of the hot paths (context/next/list/search/get/create/claim) capturing p50/p95 wall time, peak RSS, and output token count (reuse the token-counting approach from the closed pm-cu1i gate). Cold vs warm split matters: first-invocation cost vs memoized reads (~2x warm-read effect, PR#421). Emit one JSON report artifact per tier.\n\nS3 published baseline (~60m): commit the report under docs/ + record headline numbers as a note on pm-9rxu; declare per-tier budgets (e.g. context p95 and token ceiling at 1M items) - budgets are the epic's success metric, numbers before optimization.\n\nS4 regression gate (~120m): 10k tier in PR CI (seconds), 100k/1M tiers nightly; fail on budget regression beyond tolerance band. Nightly is the sole oracle for the big tiers (same pattern as the macOS matrix gap, GH-510).\n\nSequencing: S1+S2 are spike-able now with zero deps; S3/S4 gate everything downstream (pm-801d index, pm-dfg0 pagination, pm-0qg5 fan-out, pm-lvyd claim throughput all need before/after numbers). Risk: synthetic-shape realism - mitigated by deriving distributions from the real workspace rather than inventing them."
  "2026-07-11T10:38:41.683Z",maintainer-agent,"S2 measurement-target extension (2026-07-11 perf brainstorm; ledger note on pm-9rxu). Beyond the hot-path list (context/next/list/search/get/create/claim), the S2 runner should also capture, per tier:\n- Governance reads: validate, health, deps --summary, aggregate, stats wall time — agent-facing too, and health has silently 2x'd before (pm-c90s).\n- Per-phase attribution via the EXISTING OTEL span surface: startup (compile-cache cold vs warm), settings read, workspace scan/parse, serialize, extension activation. Watch pm-25se (exporter can hold the process open).\n- Git subprocess count + cumulative subprocess wall time per command (named in the program map).\n- Semantic/BM25 index refresh throughput: time-to-fresh after one mutation and after bulk generation — background-refresh queue behavior at 100k+ items is unknown.\n- Extension residual: identical command bare vs with the 11 bundled packages (shipped pm-4oww fix left ~150ms residual).\n- MCP warm-process vs CLI cold-start delta: same operation via MCP tool call vs subprocess — quantifies the sanctioned warm path (ADR pm-i7i4 forbids a daemon).\n- Output token counts are a first-class perf metric for the agent path (tokens = latency), not just the pm-cu1i gate reused."
body: ""
